12:29.792 --> 12:32.667
to make him more huggable.

12:33.750 --> 12:35.166
( laughs )

12:35.208 --> 12:36.500
Oh, I'm so glad you're okay.

12:36.542 --> 12:38.208
( grunts )

12:38.250 --> 12:39.500
CHASE:

12:38.250 --> 12:39.500
The Burnses, in general,

12:39.542 --> 12:41.291
are an affectionate family.

12:43.375 --> 12:44.792
Not gonna make this a habit

12:43.375 --> 12:44.792
or nothing,

12:44.834 --> 12:46.667
but give me a hug.

12:46.709 --> 12:48.542
It's okay,

12:46.709 --> 12:48.542
you don't have to--

12:48.583 --> 12:50.417
Okay.

12:50.458 --> 12:52.709
Although human affection

12:50.458 --> 12:52.709
is sometimes expressed

12:52.750 --> 12:54.208
in other ways.

12:54.250 --> 12:56.208
( both laugh )

12:56.250 --> 12:59.208
This gesture appears to be

12:56.250 --> 12:59.208
universal in sibling relations.

12:59.250 --> 13:01.291
Now that I get.

13:01.333 --> 13:03.875
It's true, humans do get

13:01.333 --> 13:03.875
into a lot of trouble.

13:03.917 --> 13:06.166
But that's one of the reasons

13:03.917 --> 13:06.166
we're here.

13:06.208 --> 13:07.542
Has anybody else

13:06.208 --> 13:07.542
ever noticed

13:07.583 --> 13:11.333
how Cody seems to attract

13:07.583 --> 13:11.333
falling objects?

13:11.375 --> 13:12.834
Noticed and catalogued.

13:14.750 --> 13:16.709
The roof's

13:14.750 --> 13:16.709
about to collapse.

13:21.250 --> 13:22.583
( gasps )

13:31.625 --> 13:34.417
All right, I get it,

13:31.625 --> 13:34.417
you've all become friends.

13:34.458 --> 13:36.750
But I still think,

13:34.458 --> 13:36.750
for the most part,

13:36.792 --> 13:39.166
humans are just silly.

13:46.291 --> 13:47.917
Okay, I'm gonna shoot

13:46.291 --> 13:47.917
over the hoop,

13:47.959 --> 13:51.291
bounce it off Blades' canopy,

13:47.959 --> 13:51.291
and back into the basket.

13:51.333 --> 13:52.667
Yeah, right.

13:51.333 --> 13:52.667
Those physics aren't possible.

13:52.709 --> 13:54.333
Can't you use

13:52.709 --> 13:54.333
Chase's windshield?

13:54.375 --> 13:56.125
If Dani says

13:54.375 --> 13:56.125
she can do it...

14:05.166 --> 14:06.917
She didn't do it.

14:06.959 --> 14:08.583
GRAHAM: Physics wins.

14:06.959 --> 14:08.583
DANI: Oh, Blades, you flinched.

14:08.625 --> 14:09.834
BLADES:

14:08.625 --> 14:09.834
You be the backboard.

14:11.542 --> 14:12.750
Blurr?

14:12.792 --> 14:14.583
What do you call

14:12.792 --> 14:14.583
that game anyway?

14:14.625 --> 14:17.500
Burns Ball. Our family

14:14.625 --> 14:17.500
just kind of made it up.

14:17.542 --> 14:20.291
Well, the Bots helped.

14:17.542 --> 14:20.291
Uh, you wanna play?

14:20.333 --> 14:22.583
I'm good here, thanks.

14:22.625 --> 14:24.333
You know,

14:22.625 --> 14:24.333
Heatwave was like that

14:24.375 --> 14:25.959
when he first came

14:24.375 --> 14:25.959
to Griffin Rock.

14:26.000 --> 14:28.959
All he wanted was for Optimus

14:26.000 --> 14:28.959
to reassign him.

14:29.000 --> 14:32.750
Hothead. Really.

14:29.000 --> 14:32.750
So why'd he stay?

14:32.792 --> 14:34.291
He got to know everybody,

14:34.333 --> 14:36.333
and kind of became

14:34.333 --> 14:36.333
part of the family.

14:36.375 --> 14:39.417
I'm more of a go-it-alone

14:36.375 --> 14:39.417
kind of Bot, kid.

14:39.458 --> 14:43.375
Not too great

14:39.458 --> 14:43.375
at this teamwork stuff.

14:43.417 --> 14:45.917
Okay, but I'm not

14:43.417 --> 14:45.917
giving up on you.

14:45.959 --> 14:48.458
Someday,

14:45.959 --> 14:48.458
when the time comes,

14:48.500 --> 14:50.166
I know you'll do

14:48.500 --> 14:50.166
the right thing.

14:54.417 --> 14:57.458
Humans. Silly and stubborn.

14:57.500 --> 14:59.709
( laughter )

15:07.041 --> 15:08.583
( tires screeching )

15:11.542 --> 15:15.333
Ha! Figured I'd find you here.

15:11.542 --> 15:15.333
Scrap surfing as usual.

15:15.375 --> 15:18.750
Well, need an audio output

15:15.375 --> 15:18.750
to finish a repurposing project.

15:18.792 --> 15:21.375
Red buttons, or yellow?

15:21.417 --> 15:23.500
Now you've made yourself right

15:21.417 --> 15:23.500
at home here, haven't you?

15:23.542 --> 15:25.417
Scrapyard's nice.

15:25.458 --> 15:27.750
And the other Bots.

15:25.458 --> 15:27.750
Even the humans.

15:27.792 --> 15:31.333
Everything and everybody

15:27.792 --> 15:31.333
seems to have a place.

15:31.375 --> 15:32.875
Not quite everybody.

15:37.500 --> 15:39.750
Figures.

15:39.792 --> 15:41.834
You're not thinking

15:39.792 --> 15:41.834
about leaving, are you?

15:41.875 --> 15:44.875
Me? Nah. Be nice to take

15:41.875 --> 15:44.875
a break, though.

15:44.917 --> 15:47.542
Ever been to Velocitron?

15:47.583 --> 15:51.458
Nice planet. All roads, no speed

15:47.583 --> 15:51.458
limits. Great spot to relax.

15:51.500 --> 15:54.709
Hm. Sounds boring.

15:51.500 --> 15:54.709
You gonna pick those up?

15:54.750 --> 15:55.917
( sighs )

15:55.959 --> 15:57.750
I gotta go unwind.

15:58.917 --> 16:00.375
( engine revs )

16:00.417 --> 16:02.542
( tires screech )

16:02.583 --> 16:04.959
( crackling )

16:07.500 --> 16:10.709
Okay, Graham.

16:07.500 --> 16:10.709
Should be ready.

16:10.750 --> 16:12.709
( console beeping )

16:12.750 --> 16:14.667
The voice chip from

16:12.750 --> 16:14.667
the window-washer platform

16:14.709 --> 16:17.542
was just what we needed

16:14.709 --> 16:17.542
to finish this upgrade.

16:17.583 --> 16:18.959
We call it

16:19.000 --> 16:21.041
the Empathically Reactive

16:19.000 --> 16:21.041
Voice-Interactive System.

16:21.083 --> 16:23.333
Or for short, ERVIS.

16:23.375 --> 16:25.458
COMPUTERIZED VOICE:

16:23.375 --> 16:25.458
My name is ERVIS.

16:25.500 --> 16:27.875
Please let me assist you.

16:27.917 --> 16:30.333
Not crazy about that voice,

16:27.917 --> 16:30.333
though.

16:30.375 --> 16:32.041
How about this one?

16:32.083 --> 16:33.583
( in Southern belle voice ):

16:32.083 --> 16:33.583
How can I help y'all,

16:33.625 --> 16:34.875
sweetheart?

16:33.625 --> 16:34.875
No, thanks.

16:34.917 --> 16:36.583
Nah.

16:36.625 --> 16:40.000
( in goofy voice ):

16:36.625 --> 16:40.000
Hi. I like you. Do you like me?

16:40.041 --> 16:41.583
Ew.

16:40.041 --> 16:41.583
Sounds pretty needy.

16:41.625 --> 16:42.750
Did I program that?

16:42.792 --> 16:44.291
( in normal voice ):

16:42.792 --> 16:44.291
Hello.

16:44.333 --> 16:45.917
What can I do for you?

16:45.959 --> 16:47.417
Nice.

16:45.959 --> 16:47.417
I like it.

16:47.458 --> 16:49.000
CHIEF:

16:47.458 --> 16:49.000
Team, we just got a call

16:49.041 --> 16:51.458
about a race car

16:49.041 --> 16:51.458
running red lights in town.

16:51.500 --> 16:53.417
Is Blurr with you guys?

16:53.458 --> 16:55.083
No.

16:53.458 --> 16:55.083
I can't believe it.

16:55.125 --> 16:57.417
He's going around

16:55.125 --> 16:57.417
without a driver?

16:57.458 --> 16:59.875
And violating traffic laws.

16:59.917 --> 17:02.375
(  rock theme playing  )

17:03.959 --> 17:05.917
Hey!

17:05.959 --> 17:07.542
( tires screech )

17:09.000 --> 17:11.000
( tires screeching )

17:25.667 --> 17:27.500
( electronic beeping )

17:29.667 --> 17:31.792
What?

17:29.667 --> 17:31.792
( police sirens wailing )

17:35.125 --> 17:37.667
Whoa, Horace Burns down.

17:37.709 --> 17:39.917
Team, take care

17:37.709 --> 17:39.917
of the statue and Blurr.

17:39.959 --> 17:42.000
I'll talk to Jerry.

17:45.500 --> 17:48.166
Uh, Chief,

17:45.500 --> 17:48.166
nobody's at the wheel.

17:48.208 --> 17:50.792
It's Doc Greene's

17:48.208 --> 17:50.792
new experiment.

17:50.834 --> 17:53.917
A self-driving car

17:50.834 --> 17:53.917
that makes racing safer.

17:53.959 --> 17:55.959
I think it still needs

17:53.959 --> 17:55.959
some work.

17:56.000 --> 17:57.750
CHIEF:

17:56.000 --> 17:57.750
I'll tell Doc you said so.

18:01.834 --> 18:04.834
I've never seen Heatwave

18:01.834 --> 18:04.834
so mad.

18:04.875 --> 18:06.875
Not even Kade

18:04.875 --> 18:06.875
upsets him like that.

18:12.583 --> 18:13.875
( grunts )

18:13.917 --> 18:16.709
Hey! You gonna

18:13.917 --> 18:16.709
put me down?

18:16.750 --> 18:19.500
No talking. No transforming.

18:16.750 --> 18:19.500
Drive slow.

18:20.875 --> 18:23.000
Firehouse. Now.

18:27.458 --> 18:29.208
( machinery whirring

18:27.458 --> 18:29.208
and beeping )

18:29.250 --> 18:32.542
It was one

18:29.250 --> 18:32.542
little accident.

18:32.583 --> 18:34.083
Two. First the window washer,

18:34.125 --> 18:37.166
now you put us all in danger

18:34.125 --> 18:37.166
by nearly blowing our cover.

18:37.208 --> 18:39.041
Well, I wouldn't have crashed

18:37.208 --> 18:39.041
if you'd just let me--

18:39.083 --> 18:41.166
No more excuses.

18:41.208 --> 18:43.750
You're the one responsible

18:41.208 --> 18:43.750
for your actions.

18:43.792 --> 18:45.875
Until you get that through

18:43.792 --> 18:45.875
your thick metal head,

18:45.917 --> 18:47.959
you stay at the firehouse.

18:45.917 --> 18:47.959
Got it?

18:48.000 --> 18:50.583
Oh, confinement. Really?

18:50.625 --> 18:53.041
Taking the easy way out,

18:50.625 --> 18:53.041
aren't ya?

18:53.083 --> 18:56.417
Believe me,

18:53.083 --> 18:56.417
nothing about you is easy.

18:57.291 --> 18:59.500
Thanks for your support,

18:57.291 --> 18:59.500
everybody.

19:02.750 --> 19:04.125
Good, you're back.

19:04.166 --> 19:06.625
I put in that laser component

19:04.166 --> 19:06.625
on the Sigma.

19:06.667 --> 19:08.083
We'll take a look.

19:15.875 --> 19:18.458
BLURR:

19:15.875 --> 19:18.458
This has been here

19:15.875 --> 19:18.458
the whole time?

19:20.041 --> 19:21.208
BLADES:

19:20.041 --> 19:21.208
Here you are!

19:21.250 --> 19:22.625
Um, I heard about you

19:22.667 --> 19:24.583
not being able to leave

19:22.667 --> 19:24.583
the firehouse.

19:24.625 --> 19:26.792
But that's perfect,

19:24.625 --> 19:26.792
because I just finished

19:26.834 --> 19:28.917
my training video!

19:28.959 --> 19:31.166
Look, Blades,

19:28.959 --> 19:31.166
now's not the best time to--

19:31.208 --> 19:32.917
What else do you

19:31.208 --> 19:32.917
have to do?

19:32.959 --> 19:34.667
Come on, everybody.

19:34.709 --> 19:37.542
Rescue Bots Academy

19:34.709 --> 19:37.542
is back in session.

19:37.583 --> 19:40.709
I-I think I'll sit

19:37.583 --> 19:40.709
this one out.

19:49.667 --> 19:52.667
Okay, everybody

19:49.667 --> 19:52.667
get comfortable.

19:52.709 --> 19:53.959
We ready?

19:54.000 --> 19:58.125
'Cause this is epic.

19:58.166 --> 20:00.166
CHASE: Just get this over with.

19:58.166 --> 20:00.166
DANI: Hit it, Blades.

20:05.959 --> 20:07.625
( grunts )

20:07.667 --> 20:09.709
( helicopter blades whirring )

20:10.250 --> 20:13.125
CHASE:

20:10.250 --> 20:13.125
Blades, I cannot help but notice

20:13.166 --> 20:16.792
that all of these examples

20:13.166 --> 20:16.792
are focused on you.

20:16.834 --> 20:18.208
BLADES:

20:16.834 --> 20:18.208
Well, yeah.

20:18.250 --> 20:21.542
How else are they going to learn

20:18.250 --> 20:21.542
to do air rescues?

20:21.583 --> 20:24.250
CHASE:

20:21.583 --> 20:24.250
But neither Blurr

20:21.583 --> 20:24.250
nor Salvage can fly.

20:24.291 --> 20:25.917
SALVAGE:

20:24.291 --> 20:25.917
I could probably rig up

20:25.959 --> 20:27.709
one of those scoop

20:25.959 --> 20:27.709
attachments.

20:27.750 --> 20:30.125
BLADES:

20:27.750 --> 20:30.125
Shh. This is my favorite part.

20:30.166 --> 20:32.083
With a slo-mo replay.

20:32.125 --> 20:33.625
Well, since you asked.

20:33.667 --> 20:35.667
DANI ( on screen ):

20:33.667 --> 20:35.667
Spin! Hard!

20:35.709 --> 20:39.041
BLADES ( on screen ):

20:35.709 --> 20:39.041
Whoo-hoo!

20:41.792 --> 20:43.834
HEATWAVE:

20:41.792 --> 20:43.834
I'm still waiting

20:41.792 --> 20:43.834
to hear from Optimus.

20:43.875 --> 20:45.166
But as soon as I do...

20:45.208 --> 20:46.667
CHIEF:

20:45.208 --> 20:46.667
It's your team, Heatwave.

20:46.709 --> 20:47.875
Your decision.

20:47.917 --> 20:50.792
And I've made it.

20:47.917 --> 20:50.792
Blurr has to go.

20:52.291 --> 20:55.625
What do you know?

20:52.291 --> 20:55.625
We do agree on something.

21:00.625 --> 21:01.792
Blurr?

21:01.834 --> 21:03.875
Where'd he go?

21:06.625 --> 21:08.792
( rumbling )

21:08.834 --> 21:10.083
Blurr, wait!

21:11.125 --> 21:12.250
Whoa!

21:12.291 --> 21:13.291
( grunts )

21:17.917 --> 21:19.875
(  suspenseful theme playing  )

21:22.750 --> 21:24.250
( grunts )

21:25.333 --> 21:27.834
This is not good.

21:32.000 --> 21:34.333
(  dramatic theme playing  )
